                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13096240" author="xedin" created="Fri, 2 Sep 2011 19:45:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Evaldo, please confirm that this fixed the problem!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13098086" author="jbellis" created="Tue, 6 Sep 2011 15:27:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Does this handle an upgraded 0.7 schema that didn&apos;t have replication_factor set in strategy_options?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13098105" author="xedin" created="Tue, 6 Sep 2011 15:47:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;makes sure to include &quot;replication_factor&quot; if set as an attribute to the strategy_options.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13098116" author="jbellis" created="Tue, 6 Sep 2011 15:57:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The existing backwards compatibility code in KSMetadata doesn&apos;t cover this?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(No, I don&apos;t know the answer to these questions.)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13098121" author="xedin" created="Tue, 6 Sep 2011 16:05:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Oh, I overlooked that - it actually does add replication_factor to the strategy_options.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13098137" author="jbellis" created="Tue, 6 Sep 2011 16:23:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I also note that the original report shows &quot;... and ... with ... and ...&quot; in the create statement.  Is there a second bug?  The first option should always be &quot;with.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13098149" author="xedin" created="Tue, 6 Sep 2011 16:40:58 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;I also note that the original report shows &quot;... and ... with ... and ...&quot; in the create statement. Is there a second bug? The first option should always be &quot;with.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It was fixed with removal of replication_strategy - writeAttr(...) call there had a wrong second argument.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13098157" author="xedin" created="Tue, 6 Sep 2011 16:50:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13098182" author="hudson" created="Tue, 6 Sep 2011 17:29:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated in Cassandra-0.8 #316 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://builds.apache.org/job/Cassandra-0.8/316/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://builds.apache.org/job/Cassandra-0.8/316/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
